text: Interstate 41 (I-41) is a highway in the Midwestern states of Wisconsin and Illinois in the United States. The highway goes north-south from Russell, Illinois to Howard, Wisconsin. The highway also goes through the Wisconsin cities of Green Bay, Oshkosh, Fond du Lac, and Milwaukee. The highway also connects to other major highways, such as I-94 and I-43. ==References== 41
